{
  "texts": [
    "Time periods shown are March 2018 for guns (left), June 2018 for immigration (center) and LGBTQ rights (right).",
    "Raw counts of core framing tasks are shown in the top row and as a proportion of relevant tweets in the bottom row.",
    "The March for Our Lives demonstrations occurred on March 24, shown by the black vertical line in the leftmost plots.",
    "The line in the center plots at June 20 is when Trump signed an executive order ending family separation.",
    "The line in the rightmost plots occurs at June 24, the date of Pride parades in many U.S. cities including NYC, Chicago, and San Francisco."
  ]
}